<subSubSection id="5DCA0485FFF2FF8CB1AD5594FCE9FAC2" pageId="125" pageNumber="126" type="discussion">
<paragraph id="156F570EFFF2FF8CB1AD5594FE3DFB0A" blockId="125.[151,1437,150,1293]" pageId="125" pageNumber="126">
<emphasis id="27A48B1CFFF2FF8CB1AD5594FEE4FBDF" bold="true" box="[199,328,1014,1040]" pageId="125" pageNumber="126">Comments</emphasis>
: 
<bibRefCitation id="71412AFFFFF2FF8CB0305595FD75FBDE" author="Danzig, E. M. &amp; Gavrilov-Zimin, I. A." box="[346,729,1014,1041]" pageId="125" pageNumber="126" refId="ref87819" refString="Danzig, E. M. &amp; Gavrilov-Zimin, I. A. (2015) Palaearctic mealybugs (Homoptera: Coccinea: Pseudococcidae). Part 2: Subfamily Pseudococcinae. Russian Academy of Sciences, Zoological Institute, St. Petersburg, 619 pp. https: // doi. org / 10.31610 / zsr / 2015.24.2.236" type="book" year="2015">Danzig &amp; Gavrilov-Zimin (2015)</bibRefCitation>
proposed several generic changes in mealybug classification, including placing most species of 
<taxonomicName id="D2D02C8DFFF2FF8CB3725279FD4AFBFA" authority="Ferris" authorityName="Ferris" box="[536,742,1051,1077]" class="Insecta" family="Pseudococcidae" genus="Spilococcus" kingdom="Animalia" order="Hemiptera" pageId="125" pageNumber="126" phylum="Arthropoda" rank="genus">
<emphasis id="27A48B1CFFF2FF8CB3725279FD32FBFA" box="[536,670,1051,1077]" italics="true" pageId="125" pageNumber="126">Spilococcus</emphasis>
Ferris
</taxonomicName>
in the older genus 
<taxonomicName id="D2D02C8DFFF2FF8CB2D55279FAB3FBFA" authority="Goux. Examination" authorityName="Goux. Examination" box="[959,1311,1051,1077]" class="Insecta" family="Pseudococcidae" genus="Atrococcus" kingdom="Animalia" order="Hemiptera" pageId="125" pageNumber="126" phylum="Arthropoda" rank="genus">
<emphasis id="27A48B1CFFF2FF8CB2D55279FB90FBFA" box="[959,1084,1051,1077]" italics="true" pageId="125" pageNumber="126">Atrococcus</emphasis>
Goux. Examination
</taxonomicName>
of phylogenies using molecular and morphological characters (
<bibRefCitation id="71412AFFFFF2FF8CB38C525DFC00FB96" author="Hardy, N. B. &amp; Gullan, P. J. &amp; Hodgson, C. J." box="[742,940,1087,1113]" pageId="125" pageNumber="126" pagination="51 - 71" refId="ref91117" refString="Hardy, N. B., Gullan, P. J. &amp; Hodgson, C. J. (2008) A subfamily-level classification of mealybugs (Hemiptera: Pseudococcidae) based on integrated molecular and morphological data. Systematic Entomology, 33, 51 - 71. https: // doi. org / 10.1111 / j. 1365 - 3113.2007.00408. x" type="journal article" year="2008">
Hardy 
<emphasis id="27A48B1CFFF2FF8CB25E525DFCC8FB96" box="[820,868,1087,1113]" italics="true" pageId="125" pageNumber="126">et al</emphasis>
. 2008
</bibRefCitation>
; Kaydan 
<emphasis id="27A48B1CFFF2FF8CB579525DFBE8FB96" box="[1043,1092,1087,1113]" italics="true" pageId="125" pageNumber="126">et al</emphasis>
. 2015) or molecular characters alone (
<bibRefCitation id="71412AFFFFF2FF8CB1895201FE5EFBB2" author="Downie, D. A. &amp; Gullan, P. J." box="[227,498,1123,1149]" pageId="125" pageNumber="126" pagination="238 - 259" refId="ref88250" refString="Downie, D. A. &amp; Gullan, P. J. (2004) Phylogenetic analysis of mealybugs (Hemiptera: Coccoidea: Pseudococcidae) based on DNA sequences from three nuclear genes, and a review of the higher classification. Systematic Entomology, 29 (2), 238 - 259. https: // doi. org / 10.1111 / j. 0307 - 6970.2004.00241. x" type="journal article" year="2004">Downie &amp; Gullan 2004</bibRefCitation>
) do not agree with the above action, and it is not followed here. There is considerable variation in the number of pores and ducts in the adult female of this species (
<bibRefCitation id="71412AFFFFF2FF8CB52B52E5FA87FB6E" author="Matile-Ferrero, D." box="[1089,1323,1159,1185]" pageId="125" pageNumber="126" pagination="23 - 38" refId="ref94077" refString="Matile-Ferrero, D. (1988) Sternorrhyncha: Suborder Coccoidea of Saudi Arabia (Part 2). Fauna of Saudi Arabia, 9, 23 - 38." type="journal article" year="1988">Matile-Ferrero 1988</bibRefCitation>
; 
<bibRefCitation id="71412AFFFFF2FF8CB45D52E5FE2AFB0A" author="Williams, D. J. &amp; Moghaddam, M." pageId="125" pageNumber="126" pagination="37 - 44" refId="ref98070" refString="Williams, D. J. &amp; Moghaddam, M. (2007) A new species of Rhodania Goux (Hemiptera, Coccoidea, Pseudococcidae) and new records of two other mealybug species from Iran. Zootaxa, 1398 (1), 37 - 44. https: // doi. org / 10.11646 / zootaxa. 1398.1.4" type="journal article" year="2007">Williams &amp; Moghaddam 2007</bibRefCitation>
).
</paragraph>
